## Hero Flow Documented

1. **Page load:** 3D bowling shirt canvas initializes in studio frame with default Argyle pattern and studio lighting.
2. **File upload:** Test gradient image uploaded via file input (demo-chosen "All-Around Wrap" mode).
3. **Image render:** Gradient wrapped around full-height 2048² texture (front px512–1536, back-left/right split), visible on 3D model with procedural knit normal map + studio sheen.
4. **Smart Align invocation:** "Smart Align" button clicked; subject bounding box detected (gradient has clear luminance variance), transform computed (Tier-1 instant; Tier-2 WebGPU optional refinement).
5. **Canvas update:** 3D rendering reflects alignment, zoom/crop controls visible (sliders present but not interacted in this capture to keep video brief).

## Verification Checklist

✓ Page loads without console errors (deploy-test already verified).
✓ 3D canvas element renders with image applied (visible in all frames).
✓ File input accepts uploads (functional in capture flow).
✓ Smart Align button exists and responds to click (recorded in video).
✓ Image wrapping is visible (gradient transitions from front to back on shirt).
✓ Frames are distinct and substantial (MB+ PNGs, not blank).
✓ Video is recordable and coherent (natural flow, no hangs).

